{
  "page": "Wagon",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>A <b>wagon</b> is a heavy four-wheeled vehicle pulled by draught <a href=\"/index.php/Bestiary\" title=\"Bestiary\">animals</a>. It is used for transporting goods, commodities, agricultural materials, supplies, and sometimes people. A <a href=\"/index.php/Wayn\" title=\"Wayn\">wayn</a> is a type of wagon pulled by <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a> or oxen and used for agricultural purposes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Culture\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Culture</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Game_of_Thrones\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#A_Storm_of_Swords\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#A_Feast_for_Crows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Notes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Notes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Culture\">Culture</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wagon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Culture\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Due to their heavy weight, wagons and <a href=\"/index.php/Wheelhouse\" title=\"Wheelhouse\">wheelhouses</a> are much slower than riders.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">Ironmongers</a> sell blades and razors from their wagons in the <a href=\"/index.php/Street_of_Steel\" title=\"Street of Steel\">Street of Steel</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Two wagons can pass abreast on the stone bridge of the <a href=\"/index.php/Twins\" title=\"Twins\">Twins</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot59.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> and three on the <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrian_roads\" title=\"Valyrian roads\">Valyrian roads</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Essos\" title=\"Essos\">Essos</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> The <a href=\"/index.php/Long_Bridge\" title=\"Long Bridge\">Long Bridge</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Volantis\" title=\"Volantis\">Volantis</a> has buildings along both sides of its roadway, making the road barely wide enough for two wagons to pass side by side.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wagon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>During his <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon%27s_Conquest\" title=\"Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">conquest</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_the_Conqueror\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Aegon the Conqueror\">Aegon the Conqueror</a> ordered that the <a href=\"/index.php/Sword\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sword\">swords</a> of his enemies be brought by wagons to the <a href=\"/index.php/Aegonfort\" title=\"Aegonfort\">Aegonfort</a>. Aegon later used the swords to build the <a href=\"/index.php/Iron_Throne\" title=\"Iron Throne\">Iron Throne</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabaegon.27s_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/43_AC\" title=\"43 AC\">43&#160;AC</a>, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_the_Uncrowned\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Aegon the Uncrowned\">Aegon the Uncrowned</a> and his sister-wife, Princess <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Aenys_I)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Aenys I)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a>, infiltrated King's Landing incognito using a wagon pulled by mules. They left the city on <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragonback</a>, however.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_sons_of_the_dragon.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/136_AC\" title=\"136 AC\">136&#160;AC</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Hand_of_the_King\" title=\"Hand of the King\">Hand of the King</a>, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Torrhen_Manderly\" title=\"Torrhen Manderly\">Torrhen Manderly</a>, organized a great <a href=\"/index.php/Royal_progress\" title=\"Royal progress\">royal progress</a> to mark the <a href=\"/index.php/Coming_of_age\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Coming of age\">coming of age</a> of King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon III Targaryen</a>. Among the preparations, he ordered the royal wagons and wheelhouses to be repaired and repainted. However, when Aegon came of age, he cancelled the progress.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_lysene_spring_and_the_end_of_regency.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the shipwreck of <i><a href=\"/index.php/Windproud\" title=\"Windproud\">Windproud</a></i> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_278_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">278&#160;AC</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Jommy\" title=\"Jommy\">Jommy</a> was one of the men sent to reclaim the corpses that washed up on the shore. He grabbed <a href=\"/index.php/Patchface\" title=\"Patchface\">Patchface</a> to put him into a burial wagon with the others corpses, but the boy spat up water and sat up. In the end, Patchface was the only survivor of the shipwreck.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok0.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wagon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Game_of_Thrones\"><i>A Game of Thrones</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wagon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Game of Thrones\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Arya_Stark\" title=\"Arya Stark\">Arya Stark</a> likes to ride along wagons and talk to people during her journey from <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> to <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a>. On her way to the capital, Arya befriends <a href=\"/index.php/Mycah\" title=\"Mycah\">Mycah</a>, a butcher's son who sleeps in the meat wagon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot15.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After the <a href=\"/index.php/Arrest_of_Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Arrest of Eddard Stark\">arrest</a> of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Eddard_Stark\" title=\"Eddard Stark\">Eddard Stark</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_cloaks\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Red cloaks\">Red cloaks</a> are looking for his daughter Arya. She spies on some of them searching wagons and carriages at the <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Gate\" title=\"King&#39;s Gate\">King's Gate</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot65.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Leo_Lefford\" title=\"Leo Lefford\">Leo Lefford</a> is in charge of the wagons in the <a href=\"/index.php/Westermen\" title=\"Westermen\">westermen</a> army led by Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Tywin_Lannister\" title=\"Tywin Lannister\">Tywin Lannister</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot62.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot62.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-13\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wagon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jaqen_Wagon.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/5e/Jaqen_Wagon.jpg/350px-Jaqen_Wagon.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"233\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/5e/Jaqen_Wagon.jpg/525px-Jaqen_Wagon.jpg 1.5x, /images/5/5e/Jaqen_Wagon.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Jaqen_Wagon.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Jaqen chained to the wagon - by Amok ©</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Yoren\" title=\"Yoren\">Yoren</a> and his recruits leave King's Landing with five wagons laden with supplies for the <a href=\"/index.php/Wall\" title=\"Wall\">Wall</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok1.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-14\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/index.php/Jaqen_H%27ghar\" title=\"Jaqen H&#39;ghar\">Jaqen H'ghar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Rorge\" title=\"Rorge\">Rorge</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Biter\" title=\"Biter\">Biter</a> are judged too dangerous by Yoren, and are kept chained at the back of a wagon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok5.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-15\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Amory_Lorch\" title=\"Amory Lorch\">Amory Lorch</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Storming_of_the_Gods_Eye_town_holdfast\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Storming of the Gods Eye town holdfast\">storms and burns</a> a <a href=\"/index.php/Gods_Eye_town\" title=\"Gods Eye town\">holdfast</a> where Yoren's group was staying, Arya frees Jaqen, Rorge, and Biter from their chains.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_16-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-16\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Petyr_Baelish\" title=\"Petyr Baelish\">Petyr Baelish</a>'s tenure as <a href=\"/index.php/Master_of_coin\" title=\"Master of coin\">master of coin</a>, he bought wagons with the royal treasury, amongst other things.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_17-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-17\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Gregor_Clegane\" title=\"Gregor Clegane\">Gregor Clegane</a> brings back nine wagons of salt fish to <a href=\"/index.php/Harrenhal\" title=\"Harrenhal\">Harrenhal</a> after his foraging of the <a href=\"/index.php/Riverlands\" title=\"Riverlands\">riverlands</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_18-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-18\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Silent_sisters\" title=\"Silent sisters\">Silent sisters</a> wrap the corpse of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Medger_Cerwyn\" title=\"Medger Cerwyn\">Medger Cerwyn</a> in a cloak of <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silk</a> decorated with the battle-axe <a href=\"/index.php/Sigil\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sigil\">sigil</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Cerwyn\" title=\"House Cerwyn\">House Cerwyn</a>, and load him into their wagon. Arya Stark sees them leave Harrenhal, presumably to return him home.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_19-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok30.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-19\">&#91;18&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Storm_of_Swords\"><i>A Storm of Swords</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wagon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Storm of Swords\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> parleys with <a href=\"/index.php/Mero\" title=\"Mero\">Mero</a>, the Commander of the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Sons\" title=\"Second Sons\">Second Sons</a>, outside of <a href=\"/index.php/Yunkai\" title=\"Yunkai\">Yunkai</a>. After they trade insults, Daenerys gifts him a wagon of <a href=\"/index.php/Wine\" title=\"Wine\">wine</a>, as a strategy to make the Second Sons too drunk to fight in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_near_Yunkai\" title=\"Battle near Yunkai\">battle near Yunkai</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_20-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-20\">&#91;19&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Walder_Frey\" title=\"Walder Frey\">Walder Frey</a> provides wagons of wine, ale, and mead to the common soldiers of <a href=\"/index.php/Robb_Stark\" title=\"Robb Stark\">Robb Stark</a>'s army on the occasion of the <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Wedding\" title=\"Red Wedding\">wedding</a> of his daughter, <a href=\"/index.php/Roslin_Frey\" title=\"Roslin Frey\">Roslin</a>, to Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Edmure_Tully\" title=\"Edmure Tully\">Edmure Tully</a>. Walder's generous gifts have the purpose of inebriating the <a href=\"/index.php/House_Stark\" title=\"House Stark\">Starks</a> soldiers to facilitate his planned betrayal.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_21-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-21\">&#91;20&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Feast_for_Crows\"><i>A Feast for Crows</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wagon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Feast for Crows\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Shadrich\" title=\"Shadrich\">Shadrich</a> is hired by the merchant <a href=\"/index.php/Hibald\" title=\"Hibald\">Hibald</a> to protect his wagon of goods from King's Landing to <a href=\"/index.php/Duskendale\" title=\"Duskendale\">Duskendale</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_22-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc4.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-22\">&#91;21&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The corpse of Lord Tywin Lannister leaves the capital in a tall wagon draped with crimson banners, with six silent sisters riding attendance on his bones and an honor guard of fifty <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knights</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_23-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc16.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-23\">&#91;22&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Victarion_Greyjoy\" title=\"Victarion Greyjoy\">Victarion Greyjoy</a> is disgusted when he sees survivors of the <a href=\"/index.php/Taking_of_the_Shields\" title=\"Taking of the Shields\">attack</a> on <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Hewett%27s_Town\" title=\"Lord Hewett&#39;s Town\">Lord Hewett's Town</a> putting the slain on burial wagons, as he believes men should not be buried in the ground but rather drowned in the sea.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_24-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc29.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-24\">&#91;23&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a> plans on hiring a wagon and some horses to take <a href=\"/index.php/Gilly\" title=\"Gilly\">Gilly</a> and her <a href=\"/index.php/Monster\" title=\"Monster\">son</a> (in reality <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Steelsong\" title=\"Aemon Steelsong\">Mance and Dalla's son</a>) to the safety of <a href=\"/index.php/Horn_Hill\" title=\"Horn Hill\">Horn Hill</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_25-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc45.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-25\">&#91;24&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wagon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The wayns and wagons of the baggage train of <a href=\"/index.php/Stannis_Baratheon\" title=\"Stannis Baratheon\">Stannis Baratheon</a>'s army have difficulty keeping up the pace of the <a href=\"/index.php/March_on_Winterfell\" title=\"March on Winterfell\">march on Winterfell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_26-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd42.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-26\">&#91;25&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Eddison_Tollett\" title=\"Eddison Tollett\">Dolorous Edd</a> makes the journey between <a href=\"/index.php/Long_Barrow\" title=\"Long Barrow\">Long Barrow</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Castle_Black\" title=\"Castle Black\">Castle Black</a> with six wagons to transport <a href=\"/index.php/Spearwives\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Spearwives\">spearwives</a> to their new home.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd58.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_27-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd58.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-27\">&#91;26&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>After <a href=\"/index.php/Tyrion_Lannister\" title=\"Tyrion Lannister\">Tyrion Lannister</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Penny\" title=\"Penny\">Penny</a> sign on with the Second Sons, <a href=\"/index.php/Nail\" title=\"Nail\">Nail</a> admits them to the wagons at the forge to pick out some armor from the company steel. Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Jorah_Mormont\" title=\"Jorah Mormont\">Jorah Mormont</a> also acquires new armor from the wagons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_28-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-28\">&#91;27&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wagon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The real world <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wagon\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Wagon\">wain</a> is spelled \"wayn\" in <i>A Song of Ice and Fire</i>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Wagon&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot14.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_14\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 14\">Chapter 14</a>, Catelyn III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot27.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_27\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 27\">Chapter 27</a>, Eddard VI.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot59.7B.7B.7B3.7